The paper discusses a probabilistic attack on public key cryptosystems based on the word/conjugacy problems for finitely presented groups. This topic falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the braid group from topology, which is a topic in geometric group theory (cs.GR). The use of a length function and canonical representatives suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of a scheme and attack suggests a connection to systems and control theory (cs.SY).
